title: For Sale/Trade:  Loaded Beretta 92A1.
postcontent:
I'm more of a revolver or 1911 guy (hint for trades), but I decided to purchase the A1, because it's the improved version of what parts of our military use. Replaceable sights, improved internals making recoil easier, and better handling of +P rounds, tactical rail, bulkier in places it needed, and slimmer in places it needed.

Took it shooting, and just... wasn't feeling it. So I'm seeing what else is out there before I dedicate time to getting used to how it shoots and feels. Maybe it's just because I don't do 9mm often. But no problems whatsoever.

I did purchase quite a few things with it, so hold on while I put some math out there, using prices that are commonly online.
Gun: Average is $600 from online places. I figure that even if the cheapest place has them in stock, $600 will be a great deal after FFL holding and check fees, so I'll just leave it at that for price. I paid more, since I bought from a local shop, but I'm not going to keep my reciepts just for proving a number to whiners.

Magazines: Comes with 3-17 rounders, which I shall deface a little bit to limit the round count, similar to what gunshows do, and I have 5-15 round magazines, since two rounds is the difference between a safe American, and a psycho. A bit over $100 for all 5.

TLR-1: Had to get a tactical light. Lowest on Amazon is $99.99999 or so, but I got mine for cheaper.

Cheap holster: It's mainly a house gun for me, but I got one of those cheap-O holsters.
Got it from a friend, so $free.99

And I have 100 rounds currently. Getting more when I find good deals. $30-ish.

Now's about the time that I should state that I don't really care for people sending me emails on how long or short a post should be. If you wanna only post that you have some "9milly" then that's fine. I like information. And I have nothing better to do...

All that comes out to $829, which I'd happily take, if you want to give it to me. But I think $700 would be more reasonable to start with. OBO.

Although I may just keep it, if I find some sexy wood grips for it soon...

title: For Trade:  Trading only:  Rare in pink Taurus 24/7 pro compact in .40 s&w
postcontent:
For trade is my wifes pink and black Taurus 24/7 pro semi auto in .40, with 11 to 16 round capacity depending on the magazine used.  The 24/7 pro is an amazing striker fired pistol in double/single action and features a 3 position safety (striker decocker) and internal transfer bar safety, ensuring that the gun will never fire with a round chambered.  The gun itself is equipped with a locking system on the slide itself.  Turn a key and the gun locks up completely!  After a year of owning this gun it has NEVER had a failure of any kind, and is an ideal, reliable arm for concealed carry with a 10 or 11 round magazine.  For home use, it WILL accept 15 round full sized magazines and extensions are available to fill the gap.  Included will be one extended 15 round mag with grip extension, one ten round magazine, and one eleven round magazine.  

  This model in pink is very rare as it was only made as one run exclusively for gander mountain as a limited edition special.  As such it was not priced the same as other 24/7's, and I would expect that to be taken in to account in trade offers.  Having said that I am open to most makes as long as it is reliable, but know ANYONE INTERESTED MUST MEET IN LAKELAND.  My truck is too much of a gas hog to do much driving

title: For Trade:  For Trade: Rare in pink Taurus 24/7 pro compact in .40 s&w
postcontent:
For trade is my wifes pink and black Taurus 24/7 pro semi auto in .40, with 11 to 16 round capacity depending on the magazine used. The 24/7 pro is an amazing striker fired pistol in double/single action and features a 3 position safety (striker decocker) and internal transfer bar safety, ensuring that the gun will never fire with a round chambered. The gun itself is equipped with a locking system on the slide itself. Turn a key and the gun locks up completely! After a year of owning this gun it has NEVER had a failure of any kind, and is an ideal, reliable arm for concealed carry with a 10 or 11 round magazine. For home use, it WILL accept 15 round full sized magazines and extensions are available to fill the gap. Included will be one extended 15 round mag with grip extension, one ten round magazine, and one eleven round magazine.

This model in pink is very rare as it was only made as one run exclusively for gander mountain as a limited edition special. As such it was not priced the same as other 24/7's, and I would expect that to be taken in to account in trade offers. Having said that I am open to most makes as long as it is reliable, but know ANYONE INTERESTED MUST MEET IN LAKELAND. My truck is too much of a gas hog to do much driving
